description:
Enginzyme is a Swedish venture-backed startup company building the most versatle and efficient enzyme technology platform for chemical manufacturing that the world has ever seen. Founded in 2014 in Stockholm, Sweden, we have been recognised as a Technology Pioneer by the World Economic Forum, and we are on a mission to transform the $5 trillion-worth chemical industry.                      




 We are looking for a talented and dedicated Researcher/Lead Researcher who can join our R&D team and help support our continued progress. You’ll be a part of a tight-knit and quick-moving team, where collaboration and out-of-the-box thinking is central to our achievements. The ideal candidate has a strong background in enzyme biochemistry and enzyme technology, ideally applied in industrially-relevant contexts.             




 This is a full-time, lab-focused position based in Stockholm and may include some traveling for development and training purposes.                      










 Application deadline: April 22nd, 2025

                   











**Who you are** 




 We are looking for an innovation-driven and organised PhD graduate in biotechnology, chemistry or a related field with a deep understanding and hands-on experience in chemical and enzymatic catalysis as well as protein production and characterisation. Candidates that are truly outstanding with other backgrounds and/or equivalent experience may also be considered. Any practical experience with high-throughput screening and optimisation will be considered as an additional merit. Previous experience in industrial settings will be considered as a plus.     










 In terms of personal qualities, we are looking for a friendly, approachable, and cooperative person who is passionate about what they do, gets things done, and thrives on innovation by pushing boundaries. The ideal candidate is an out-of-the-box thinker who is eager to learn from others just as much as they are eager to share their own knowledge, fostering a culture of curiosity and continuous improvement. 




 If this describes you, you’ll integrate well with the rest of the team!            










 We understand that you might not feel like you 'check all the boxes' as you read this job description. However, if this role excites you and makes you eager to learn, we encourage you to apply regardless.      










**What you will do** 





 Project execution




* Collaborate with a multidisciplinary R&D team of talented scientists and engineers to help solve important challenges;
* Autonomously design and perform experiments involving biocatalysis, reaction engineering, enzyme production, purification, characterisation and immobilisation;
* Analyse and report experimental results. Present relevant findings to the project team as well as to other internal and external stakeholders;
* Contribute to the definition of the overall technical strategy of the projects.




 Innovation




* Actively contribute to the development of enginzyme’s own technology platform;
* Collaborate with our business development team to identify novel market opportunities and support their activities as a technical expert.




 Mentoring and supervision




* Informal supervision of lab technician and research assistants.









**What we can offer you** 



* The opportunity to be part of something big and impactful;
* A chance to advance state-of-the-art technology;
* An environment where you’re free — and expected — to continuously learn and grow;
* Start-up mentality with minimal red tape, providing substantial responsibility and ownership;
* Flexible hours;
* The opportunity to work with a friendly, very multi-cultural, tight-knit group of world-class researchers and engineers;
* A competitive salary and company equity;
* 25 days of paid annual leave, comprehensive occupational health, injury, and life insurance, along with a robust occupational pension plan;
* Seamless access to Sweden's renowned healthcare and childcare systems, ensuring peace of mind for you and your family;
* One of the best cities in the world to live and work, and we offer relocation support to help you get set up. But don’t take our word for it; check out this short video to hear firsthand about the quality of life in Stockholm: https://youtu.be/CAkdWUjdJyA.









**Notes on the hiring process** 



* Applications will be reviewed no earlier than the application deadline.
* Applications received via any channel other than the official application form will not be considered.
